2026-04-15T06:18:13.609Z JOT-0048-0F comment.added "Done. Added jot-core::config module (strict schema via deny_unknown_fields, YAML round-trip validation, layered load defaults < global < local). Added jot-cli config subcommand with get/set and an optional bare-list view. set-target resolution: explicit --global/--local win; else auto-pick local if .jot/ present, global if ~/.config/jot/config.yaml exists, else fail-loud with an actionable message. Fortune call in main.rs now gated on cfg.output.fortune and passes cfg.output.fortune_category. 15 new bats cases in tests/integration/config.bats cover the full contract. Welcome text updated to use --priority rather than --prio via aliases-on-Close: infer_subcommands made c ambiguous between close/config, so Close picks up c as an explicit alias and co stays ambiguous (documented in the prefix-shortcuts test)." [ai:claude@joy delegated-by:horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
